Chagas disease and blood donations in Canada
-------------------------
According to a report on the Canadian Broadcasting Corporation's
Radio one program the Current, (aired 19 Nov 2003) it's 5 cases in US
and 2 cases in Canada, both in Manitoba. The cases were both
immunocompromised by chemotherapy for cancer. One case, a child, died
shortly after acquiring Chagas through transfusion of blood products,
but may have died of complications of his underlying illness -- this
was 17 years ago. The other case received the Chagas treatment
protocol recommended by CDC-Atlanta, survived Chagas, but eventually
succumbed to the cancer. The donors were both non-Hispanic with
history of travel or residence in Latin America, no history of
symptoms, and no symptoms at time of blood donation. More info will
likely be posted later on the CBC website.
--
Dominique Charron, PhD DVM
